.TH REAC-AES67 8 "2026-06-14" "reac-aes67 0.3.0" "System Manager's Manual"
.SH NAME
reac-aes67 \- bridge a Roland REAC stream to AES67 (RTP L24 multicast)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B reac-aes67
.B \-\-listen
.I IFACE
.B \-\-udp
.I GROUP:PORT
.RB [ \-\-rate
.IR auto | 48000 | 96000 | 44100 ]
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B reac-aes67
.B \-\-pcap
.I FILE
.RB ( \-\-udp
.IR GROUP:PORT " | " \-\-dump\-samples " | " \-\-count\-rtp )
.br
.B reac-aes67
.B \-\-print\-sdp
.B \-\-udp
.I GROUP:PORT
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B reac-aes67
decodes a Roland REAC stream (audio-over-Ethernet, EtherType 0x8819) captured on a LAN
interface and re-emits all 40 channels as an AES67 RTP L24 multicast stream that
PipeWire and other AES67 receivers can subscribe to \(em to record, monitor, or route.
It is receive-only on REAC: it never transmits a REAC frame, so it cannot disturb a
live wired REAC link.
.PP
reac-aes67 decodes the master's DOWNSTREAM broadcast \(em the program the console
sends out, a fixed 40-channel frame that is rate-invariant (40 ch x 12 samples at
every rate; the sample rate is the packet rate, pps = rate / 12: 3675 / 4000 / 8000 at
44.1 / 48 / 96 kHz). A stagebox's UPSTREAM return is different: it carries the box's
own input count (variable per box, a smaller frame) and its channel map is
FPGA-scrambled, so decoding that is out of scope here. See the REAC wire-format
reference at
.UR https://github.com/FreeREAC/reac-protocol
.UE .
.SH OPTIONS
.SS Source (one required)
.TP
.BI \-\-listen " IFACE"
Live AF_PACKET capture on IFACE. Needs CAP_NET_RAW (root, or the packaged
capabilities file on OpenWrt).
.TP
.BI \-\-pcap " FILE"
Replay a classic libpcap capture through the full pipeline (no real-time pacing).
.TP
.B \-\-gen\-tone
Emit a synthetic 40-channel tone (bench test; no REAC hardware). Requires --udp.
.SS Output
.TP
.BI \-\-udp " GROUP:PORT"
AES67 RTP destination (multicast group + UDP port). Required for every sending mode;
no default. Egress goes to whichever network owns the route to GROUP \(em put GROUP on
a separate bridge/VLAN from REAC.
.TP
.BI \-\-rate " auto|48000|96000|44100"
REAC sample rate. With
.B auto
(\-\-listen only) the rate is measured from the live packet cadence and snapped to the
nearest standard rate; otherwise set it explicitly to match the clock master. Default
48000.
.TP
.BI \-\-name " NAME"
Stream / SDP session name. Default REAC.
.TP
.BI \-\-pt " N"
RTP payload type. Default 97.
.TP
.BI \-\-ssrc " HEX"
RTP SSRC, parsed as hex. Default 11223344.
.TP
.BI \-\-ttl " N"
Multicast TTL (minimum 1). Default 1.
.TP
.BI \-\-origin " IP"
SDP origin (o=) IP. Default 0.0.0.0.
.TP
.B \-\-bcast\-only
Decode only the master broadcast (downstream), ignoring the unicast upstream return \(em
use when both directions share the capture interface.
.TP
.BI \-\-iface " DEV"
Pin the multicast egress interface (otherwise route-table-driven).
.TP
.BI \-\-plc\-xfade " N" ", " \fB\-\-plc\-fade\fP " N"
Packet-loss-concealment crossfade / fade window (\-\-listen only).
.TP
.B \-\-no\-sap
Disable the periodic SAP announcement (RFC 2974 AES67 discovery; on by default).
.SS Inspect / offline
.TP
.B \-\-print\-sdp
Print the RFC 4566 / AES67 SDP for the stream (needs --udp) and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-dump\-samples
Decode a --pcap and print 24-bit samples per frame (no RTP).
.TP
.B \-\-count\-rtp
Decode a --pcap and print the RTP / concealed packet counts.
.SS Dante-interop profile
.TP
.B \-\-profile dante
48 kHz, 1 ms packets, up to 8-channel flows, RFC 7273 SDP to the Dante SAP group;
needs a PTPv2-slaved bridge. See also
.BR \-\-aes67\-base ", " \-\-rtp\-port ", " \-\-ch\-per\-flow ", " \-\-gmid ", " \-\-ptp\-domain .
.SH RECORDING A WIRED REAC NETWORK
To record a mixer's REAC channels off an existing wired link without disturbing it: tap
the desk's REAC output non-intrusively \(em a desk REAC split / mirror output (best), a
passive 100-Mbit Ethernet TAP, or a clean unmanaged 100BASE-TX switch \(em then run
.B reac-aes67 \-\-listen
on that tap, keeping the AES67 egress on a separate interface from the tap. reac-aes67
only listens on REAC, so the wired link is unaffected. Match
.B \-\-rate
to the desk (or use
.BR \-\-rate " " auto ).
This captures the console's downstream OUTPUT program (the 40-channel broadcast). A
stagebox's own inputs travel UPSTREAM with the box's channel count and an
FPGA-scrambled map \(em a different, open case. The full recipe is recipe (f) in the
project's docs/EXAMPLES.md.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/config/reac-aes67
UCI configuration (OpenWrt): one
.B stream
section per REAC zone.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR reac-repacer (8)
(Wi-Fi de-jitter relay). The FreeREAC project:
.UR https://github.com/FreeREAC
.UE .
